{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I was walking in the market one day with my wife,"},{"time":3000,"text":"and somebody stuck a cage in my face."},{"time":5000,"text":"And in between those slits"},{"time":7000,"text":"were the saddest eyes I've ever seen."},{"time":9000,"text":"There was a very sick orangutan baby, my first encounter."},{"time":12000,"text":"That evening I came back to the market in the dark"},{"time":15000,"text":"and I heard \"uhh, uhh,\""},{"time":18000,"text":"and sure enough I found a dying orangutan baby on a garbage heap."},{"time":23000,"text":"Of course, the cage was salvaged."},{"time":25000,"text":"I took up the little baby,"},{"time":27000,"text":"massaged her, forced her to drink"},{"time":30000,"text":"until she finally started breathing normally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33000,"text":"This is Uce."},{"time":35000,"text":"She's now living in the jungle of Sungai Wain,"},{"time":37000,"text":"and this is Matahari, her second son,"},{"time":39000,"text":"which, by the way, is also the son of the second orangutan I rescued, Dodoy."},{"time":44000,"text":"That changed my life quite dramatically,"},{"time":46000,"text":"and as of today, I have almost 1,000 babies in my two centers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":53000,"text":"No. No. No. Wrong."},{"time":55000,"text":"It's horrible. It's a proof of our failing to save them in the wild."},{"time":58000,"text":"It's not good."},{"time":60000,"text":"This is merely proof of everyone failing to do the right thing."},{"time":64000,"text":"Having more than all the orangutans in all the zoos in the world together,"},{"time":68000,"text":"just now like victims for every baby,"},{"time":71000,"text":"six have disappeared from the forest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74000,"text":"The deforestation, especially for oil palm,"},{"time":76000,"text":"to provide biofuel for Western countries"},{"time":79000,"text":"is what's causing these problems."},{"time":82000,"text":"And those are the peat swamp forests on 20 meters of peat,"},{"time":85000,"text":"the largest accumulation of organic material in the world."},{"time":88000,"text":"When you open this for growing oil palms"},{"time":91000,"text":"you're creating CO2 volcanoes"},{"time":93000,"text":"that are emitting so much CO2"},{"time":96000,"text":"that my country is now the third largest emitter of greenhouse gasses in the world,"},{"time":101000,"text":"after China and the United States."},{"time":103000,"text":"And we don't have any industry at all --"},{"time":106000,"text":"it's only because of this deforestation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"And these are horrible images."},{"time":112000,"text":"I'm not going to talk too long about it,"},{"time":114000,"text":"but there are so many of the family of Uce,"},{"time":116000,"text":"which are not so fortunate to live out there in the forest,"},{"time":120000,"text":"that still have to go through that process."},{"time":122000,"text":"And I don't know anymore where to put them."},{"time":124000,"text":"So I decided that I had to come up with a solution for her"},{"time":128000,"text":"but also a solution"},{"time":130000,"text":"that will benefit the people that are trying to exploit those forests,"},{"time":134000,"text":"to get their hands on the last timber"},{"time":137000,"text":"and that are causing, in that way,"},{"time":140000,"text":"the loss of habitat and all those victims."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143000,"text":"So I created the place Samboja Lestari,"},{"time":145000,"text":"and the idea was,"},{"time":147000,"text":"if I can do this on the worst possible place that I can think of"},{"time":150000,"text":"where there is really nothing left,"},{"time":152000,"text":"no one will have an excuse to say, \"Yeah, but ...\""},{"time":156000,"text":"No. Everyone should be able to follow this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160000,"text":"So we're in East Borneo. This is the place where I started."},{"time":165000,"text":"As you can see there's only yellow terrain."},{"time":167000,"text":"There's nothing left -- just a bit of grass there."},{"time":170000,"text":"In 2002 we had about 50 percent of the people jobless there."},{"time":174000,"text":"There was a huge amount of crime."},{"time":176000,"text":"People spent so much of their money on health issues and drinking water."},{"time":181000,"text":"There was no agricultural productivity left."},{"time":184000,"text":"This was the poorest district in the whole province"},{"time":187000,"text":"and it was a total extinction of wildlife."},{"time":190000,"text":"This was like a biological desert."},{"time":192000,"text":"When I stood there in the grass, it's hot -- not even the sound of insects --"},{"time":196000,"text":"just this waving grass."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198000,"text":"Still, four years later we have created jobs for about 3,000 people."},{"time":203000,"text":"The climate has changed. I will show you:"},{"time":206000,"text":"no more flooding, no more fires."},{"time":208000,"text":"It's no longer the poorest district,"},{"time":211000,"text":"and there is a huge development of biodiversity."},{"time":213000,"text":"We've got over 1,000 species. We have 137 bird species as of today."},{"time":219000,"text":"We have 30 species of reptiles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221000,"text":"So what happened here? We created a huge economic failure in this forest."},{"time":227000,"text":"So basically the whole process of destruction"},{"time":230000,"text":"had gone a bit slower than what is happening now with the oil palm."},{"time":233000,"text":"But we saw the same thing."},{"time":235000,"text":"We had slash and burn agriculture;"},{"time":237000,"text":"people cannot afford the fertilizer,"},{"time":239000,"text":"so they burn the trees and have the minerals available there;"},{"time":242000,"text":"the fires become more frequent,"},{"time":244000,"text":"and after a while you're stuck with an area of land"},{"time":247000,"text":"where there is no fertility left."},{"time":249000,"text":"There are no trees left."},{"time":251000,"text":"Still, in this place, in this grassland"},{"time":254000,"text":"where you can see our very first office there on that hill,"},{"time":257000,"text":"four years later, there is this one green blop on the Earth's surface ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":264000,"text":"And there are all these animals, and all these people happy,"},{"time":267000,"text":"and there's this economic value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269000,"text":"So how's this possible?"},{"time":271000,"text":"It was quite simple. If you'll look at the steps:"},{"time":273000,"text":"we bought the land, we dealt with the fire,"},{"time":275000,"text":"and then only, we started doing the reforestation"},{"time":278000,"text":"by combining agriculture with forestry."},{"time":281000,"text":"Only then we set up the infrastructure and management and the monetary."},{"time":285000,"text":"But we made sure that in every step of the way"},{"time":288000,"text":"the local people were going to be fully involved"},{"time":291000,"text":"so that no outside forces would be able to interfere with that."},{"time":295000,"text":"The people would become the defenders of that forest."},{"time":299000,"text":"So we do the \"people, profit, planet\" principles,"},{"time":301000,"text":"but we do it in addition"},{"time":303000,"text":"to a sure legal status --"},{"time":305000,"text":"because if the forest belongs to the state,"},{"time":307000,"text":"people say, \"It belongs to me, it belongs to everyone.\""},{"time":310000,"text":"And then we apply all these other principles"},{"time":313000,"text":"like transparency, professional management, measurable results,"},{"time":317000,"text":"scalability, [unclear], etc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320000,"text":"What we did was we formulated recipes --"},{"time":323000,"text":"how to go from a starting situation where you have nothing"},{"time":326000,"text":"to a target situation."},{"time":328000,"text":"You formulate a recipe based upon the factors you can control,"},{"time":333000,"text":"whether it be the skills or the fertilizer or the plant choice."},{"time":337000,"text":"And then you look at the outputs and you start measuring what comes out."},{"time":342000,"text":"Now in this recipe you also have the cost."},{"time":344000,"text":"You also know how much labor is needed."},{"time":347000,"text":"If you can drop this recipe on the map"},{"time":350000,"text":"on a sandy soil, on a clay soil,"},{"time":352000,"text":"on a steep slope, on flat soil,"},{"time":354000,"text":"you put those different recipes; if you combine them,"},{"time":357000,"text":"out of that comes a business plan,"},{"time":359000,"text":"comes a work plan, and you can optimize it"},{"time":362000,"text":"for the amount of labor you have available or for the amount of fertilizer you have,"},{"time":366000,"text":"and you can do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"This is how it looks like in practice. We have this grass we want to get rid of."},{"time":372000,"text":"It exudes [unclear]-like compounds from the roots."},{"time":375000,"text":"The acacia trees are of a very low value"},{"time":378000,"text":"but we need them to restore the micro-climate, to protect the soil"},{"time":381000,"text":"and to shake out the grasses."},{"time":384000,"text":"And after eight years they might actually yield some timber --"},{"time":387000,"text":"that is, if you can preserve it in the right way,"},{"time":390000,"text":"which we can do with bamboo peels."},{"time":392000,"text":"It's an old temple-building technique from Japan"},{"time":395000,"text":"but bamboo is very fire-susceptible."},{"time":397000,"text":"So if we would plant that in the beginning"},{"time":399000,"text":"we would have a very high risk of losing everything again."},{"time":403000,"text":"So we plant it later, along the waterways"},{"time":405000,"text":"to filter the water, provide the raw products"},{"time":407000,"text":"just in time for when the timber becomes available."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"So the idea is: how to integrate these flows"},{"time":413000,"text":"in space, over time and with the limited means you have."},{"time":418000,"text":"So we plant the trees, we plant these pineapples"},{"time":420000,"text":"and beans and ginger in between, to reduce the competition for the trees,"},{"time":424000,"text":"the crop fertilizer. Organic material is useful for the agricultural crops,"},{"time":429000,"text":"for the people, but also helps the trees. The farmers have free land,"},{"time":432000,"text":"the system yields early income, the orangutans get healthy food"},{"time":436000,"text":"and we can speed up ecosystem regeneration"},{"time":439000,"text":"while even saving some money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441000,"text":"So beautiful. What a theory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443000,"text":"But is it really that easy?"},{"time":446000,"text":"Not really, because if you looked at what happened in 1998,"},{"time":449000,"text":"the fire started."},{"time":451000,"text":"This is an area of about 50 million hectares."},{"time":453000,"text":"January."},{"time":455000,"text":"February."},{"time":457000,"text":"March."},{"time":459000,"text":"April."},{"time":460000,"text":"May."},{"time":461000,"text":"We lost 5.5 million hectares in just a matter of a few months."},{"time":465000,"text":"This is because we have 10,000 of those underground fires"},{"time":468000,"text":"that you also have in Pennsylvania here in the United States."},{"time":472000,"text":"And once the soil gets dried, you're in a dry season -- you get cracks,"},{"time":475000,"text":"oxygen goes in, flames come out and the problem starts all over again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479000,"text":"So how to break that cycle?"},{"time":481000,"text":"Fire is the biggest problem."},{"time":483000,"text":"This is what it looked like for three months."},{"time":486000,"text":"For three months, the automatic lights outside did not go off"},{"time":489000,"text":"because it was that dark."},{"time":491000,"text":"We lost all the crops. No children gained weight for over a year;"},{"time":495000,"text":"they lost 12 IQ points. It was a disaster"},{"time":498000,"text":"for orangutans and people."},{"time":500000,"text":"So these fires are really the first things to work on."},{"time":503000,"text":"That was why I put it as a single point up there."},{"time":506000,"text":"And you need the local people for that because these grasslands,"},{"time":509000,"text":"once they start burning ... It goes through it like a windstorm"},{"time":513000,"text":"and you lose again the last bit of ash and nutrients"},{"time":516000,"text":"to the first rainfall -- going to the sea"},{"time":518000,"text":"killing off the coral reefs there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"So you have to do it with the local people."},{"time":523000,"text":"That is the short-term solution but you also need a long-term solution."},{"time":526000,"text":"So what we did is, we created"},{"time":528000,"text":"a ring of sugar palms around the area."},{"time":531000,"text":"These sugar palms turn out to be fire-resistant --"},{"time":534000,"text":"also flood-resistant, by the way --"},{"time":536000,"text":"and they provide a lot of income for local people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540000,"text":"This is what it looks like:"},{"time":542000,"text":"the people have to tap them twice a day -- just a millimeter slice --"},{"time":545000,"text":"and the only thing you harvest is sugar water,"},{"time":548000,"text":"carbon dioxide, rain fall and a little bit of sunshine."},{"time":552000,"text":"In principle, you make those trees into"},{"time":554000,"text":"biological photovoltaic cells."},{"time":557000,"text":"And you can create so much energy from this --"},{"time":560000,"text":"they produce three times more energy per hectare per year,"},{"time":565000,"text":"because you can tap them on a daily basis."},{"time":567000,"text":"You don't need to harvest [unclear]"},{"time":569000,"text":"or any other of the crops."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571000,"text":"So this is the combination where we have all this genetic potential in the tropics,"},{"time":575000,"text":"which is still unexploited, and doing it in combination with technology."},{"time":579000,"text":"But also your legal side needs to be in very good order."},{"time":583000,"text":"So we bought that land,"},{"time":585000,"text":"and here is where we started our project --"},{"time":587000,"text":"in the middle of nowhere."},{"time":589000,"text":"And if you zoom in a bit you can see that all of this area"},{"time":593000,"text":"is divided into strips that go over different types of soil,"},{"time":596000,"text":"and we were actually monitoring,"},{"time":599000,"text":"measuring every single tree in these 2,000 hectares, 5,000 acres."},{"time":605000,"text":"And this forest is quite different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":608000,"text":"What I really did was I just followed nature,"},{"time":610000,"text":"and nature doesn't know monocultures,"},{"time":613000,"text":"but a natural forest is multilayered."},{"time":616000,"text":"That means that both in the ground and above the ground"},{"time":618000,"text":"it can make better use of the available light,"},{"time":621000,"text":"it can store more carbon in the system, it can provide more functions."},{"time":626000,"text":"But, it's more complicated. It's not that simple, and you have to work with the people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630000,"text":"So, just like nature,"},{"time":633000,"text":"we also grow fast planting trees and underneath that,"},{"time":636000,"text":"we grow the slower growing, primary-grain forest trees of a very high diversity"},{"time":642000,"text":"that can optimally use that light. Then,"},{"time":644000,"text":"what is just as important: get the right fungi in there"},{"time":648000,"text":"that will grow into those leaves, bring back the nutrients"},{"time":651000,"text":"to the roots of the trees that have just dropped that leaf within 24 hours."},{"time":655000,"text":"And they become like nutrient pumps."},{"time":657000,"text":"You need the bacteria to fix nitrogen,"},{"time":660000,"text":"and without those microorganisms, you won't have any performance at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665000,"text":"And then we started planting -- only 1,000 trees a day."},{"time":669000,"text":"We could have planted many, many more, but we didn't want to"},{"time":672000,"text":"because we wanted to keep the number of jobs stable."},{"time":675000,"text":"We didn't want to lose the people"},{"time":678000,"text":"that are going to work in that plantation."},{"time":682000,"text":"And we do a lot of work here."},{"time":684000,"text":"We use indicator plants to look at what soil types,"},{"time":687000,"text":"or what vegetables will grow, or what trees will grow here."},{"time":690000,"text":"And we have monitored every single one of those trees from space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695000,"text":"This is what it looks like in reality;"},{"time":697000,"text":"you have this irregular ring around it,"},{"time":699000,"text":"with strips of 100 meters wide, with sugar palms"},{"time":703000,"text":"that can provide income for 648 families."},{"time":706000,"text":"It's only a small part of the area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709000,"text":"The nursery, in here, is quite different."},{"time":712000,"text":"If you look at the number of tree species we have in Europe, for instance,"},{"time":715000,"text":"from the Urals up to England, you know how many?"},{"time":718000,"text":"165."},{"time":720000,"text":"In this nursery, we're going to grow 10 times more than the number of species."},{"time":724000,"text":"Can you imagine?"},{"time":726000,"text":"You do need to know what you are working with,"},{"time":728000,"text":"but it's that diversity which makes it work."},{"time":731000,"text":"That you can go from this zero situation,"},{"time":734000,"text":"by planting the vegetables and the trees, or directly, the trees"},{"time":738000,"text":"in the lines in that grass there,"},{"time":740000,"text":"putting up the buffer zone, producing your compost,"},{"time":743000,"text":"and then making sure that at every stage of that up growing forest"},{"time":748000,"text":"there are crops that can be used."},{"time":750000,"text":"In the beginning, maybe pineapples and beans and corn;"},{"time":752000,"text":"in the second phase, there will be bananas and papayas;"},{"time":755000,"text":"later on, there will be chocolate and chilies."},{"time":758000,"text":"And then slowly, the trees start taking over,"},{"time":760000,"text":"bringing in produce from the fruits, from the timber, from the fuel wood."},{"time":764000,"text":"And finally, the sugar palm forest takes over"},{"time":767000,"text":"and provides the people with permanent income."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"On the top left, underneath those green stripes,"},{"time":772000,"text":"you see some white dots -- those are actually individual pineapple plants"},{"time":776000,"text":"that you can see from space."},{"time":778000,"text":"And in that area we started growing some acacia trees"},{"time":783000,"text":"that you just saw before."},{"time":785000,"text":"So this is after one year."},{"time":787000,"text":"And this is after two years."},{"time":789000,"text":"And that's green. If you look from the tower --"},{"time":792000,"text":"this is when we start attacking the grass."},{"time":795000,"text":"We plant in the seedlings"},{"time":797000,"text":"mixed with the bananas, the papayas, all the crops for the local people,"},{"time":801000,"text":"but the trees are growing up fast in between as well."},{"time":804000,"text":"And three years later, 137 species of birds are living here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":813000,"text":"So we lowered air temperature three to five degrees Celsius."},{"time":817000,"text":"Air humidity is up 10 percent."},{"time":819000,"text":"Cloud cover -- I'm going to show it to you -- is up."},{"time":821000,"text":"Rainfall is up."},{"time":823000,"text":"And all these species and income."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"This ecolodge that I built here,"},{"time":827000,"text":"three years before, was an empty, yellow field."},{"time":830000,"text":"This transponder that we operate with the European Space Agency --"},{"time":834000,"text":"it gives us the benefit that every satellite that comes over to calibrate itself"},{"time":838000,"text":"is taking a picture."},{"time":840000,"text":"Those pictures we use to analyze how much carbon, how the forest is developing,"},{"time":844000,"text":"and we can monitor every tree using satellite images through our cooperation."},{"time":850000,"text":"We can use these data now"},{"time":852000,"text":"to provide other regions with recipes and the same technology."},{"time":856000,"text":"We actually have it already with Google Earth."},{"time":858000,"text":"If you would use a little bit of your technology to put tracking devices in trucks,"},{"time":862000,"text":"and use Google Earth in combination with that,"},{"time":865000,"text":"you could directly tell what palm oil has been sustainably produced,"},{"time":869000,"text":"which company is stealing the timber,"},{"time":872000,"text":"and you could save so much more carbon"},{"time":874000,"text":"than with any measure of saving energy here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":877000,"text":"So this is the Samboja Lestari area."},{"time":880000,"text":"You measure how the trees grow back,"},{"time":882000,"text":"but you can also measure the biodiversity coming back."},{"time":886000,"text":"And biodiversity is an indicator of how much water can be balanced,"},{"time":890000,"text":"how many medicines can be kept here."},{"time":893000,"text":"And finally I made it into the rain machine"},{"time":896000,"text":"because this forest is now creating its own rain."},{"time":899000,"text":"This nearby city of Balikpapan has a big problem with water;"},{"time":903000,"text":"it's 80 percent surrounded by seawater,"},{"time":906000,"text":"and we have now a lot of intrusion there."},{"time":908000,"text":"Now we looked at the clouds above this forest;"},{"time":911000,"text":"we looked at the reforestation area, the semi-open area and the open area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915000,"text":"And look at these images."},{"time":918000,"text":"I'll just run them very quickly through."},{"time":920000,"text":"In the tropics, raindrops are not formed from ice crystals,"},{"time":923000,"text":"which is the case in the temperate zones,"},{"time":925000,"text":"you need the trees with [unclear], chemicals that come out of the leaves of the trees"},{"time":930000,"text":"that initiate the raindrops."},{"time":932000,"text":"So you create a cool place where clouds can accumulate,"},{"time":936000,"text":"and you have the trees to initiate the rain."},{"time":938000,"text":"And look, there's now 11.2 percent more clouds --"},{"time":942000,"text":"already, after three years."},{"time":944000,"text":"If you look at rainfall, it was already up 20 percent at that time."},{"time":949000,"text":"Let's look at the next year,"},{"time":951000,"text":"and you can see that that trend is continuing."},{"time":953000,"text":"Where at first we had a small cap of higher rainfall,"},{"time":956000,"text":"that cap is now widening and getting higher."},{"time":959000,"text":"And if we look at the rainfall pattern"},{"time":962000,"text":"above Samboja Lestari, it used to be the driest place,"},{"time":966000,"text":"but now you see consistently see a peak of rain forming there."},{"time":970000,"text":"So you can actually change the climate."},{"time":974000,"text":"When there are trade winds of course the effect disappears,"},{"time":978000,"text":"but afterwards, as soon as the wind stabilizes,"},{"time":981000,"text":"you see again that the rainfall peaks come back above this area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985000,"text":"So to say it is hopeless is not the right thing to do,"},{"time":990000,"text":"because we actually can make that difference"},{"time":992000,"text":"if you integrate the various technologies."},{"time":996000,"text":"And it's nice to have the science, but it still depends mostly upon the people,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"on your education."},{"time":1002000,"text":"We have our farmer schools."},{"time":1004000,"text":"But the real success of course, is our band --"},{"time":1006000,"text":"because if a baby is born, we will play, so everyone's our family"},{"time":1010000,"text":"and you don't make trouble with your family."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1012000,"text":"This is how it looks."},{"time":1014000,"text":"We have this road going around the area,"},{"time":1016000,"text":"which brings the people electricity and water from our own area."},{"time":1020000,"text":"We have the zone with the sugar palms,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"and then we have this fence with very thorny palms"},{"time":1024000,"text":"to keep the orangutans -- that we provide with a place to live in the middle --"},{"time":1029000,"text":"and the people apart."},{"time":1031000,"text":"And inside, we have this area for reforestation"},{"time":1033000,"text":"as a gene bank to keep all that material alive,"},{"time":1036000,"text":"because for the last 12 years"},{"time":1038000,"text":"not a single seedling of the tropical hardwood trees has grown up"},{"time":1042000,"text":"because the climatic triggers have disappeared."},{"time":1045000,"text":"All the seeds get eaten."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1047000,"text":"So now we do the monitoring on the inside --"},{"time":1049000,"text":"from towers, satellites, ultralights."},{"time":1052000,"text":"Each of the families that have sold their land now get a piece of land back."},{"time":1056000,"text":"And it has two nice fences of tropical hardwood trees --"},{"time":1060000,"text":"you have the shade trees planted in year one,"},{"time":1062000,"text":"then you underplanted with the sugar palms,"},{"time":1065000,"text":"and you plant this thorny fence."},{"time":1067000,"text":"And after a few years, you can remove some of those shade trees."},{"time":1071000,"text":"The people get that acacia timber which we have preserved with the bamboo peel,"},{"time":1075000,"text":"and they can build a house, they have some fuel wood to cook with."},{"time":1078000,"text":"And they can start producing from the trees as many as they like."},{"time":1082000,"text":"They have enough income for three families."},{"time":1086000,"text":"But whatever you do in that program, it has to be fully supported by the people,"},{"time":1090000,"text":"meaning that you also have to adjust it to the local, cultural values."},{"time":1094000,"text":"There is no simple one recipe for one place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1098000,"text":"You also have to make sure that it is very difficult to corrupt --"},{"time":1102000,"text":"that it's transparent."},{"time":1104000,"text":"Like here, in Samboja Lestari,"},{"time":1106000,"text":"we divide that ring in groups of 20 families."},{"time":1109000,"text":"If one member trespasses the agreement,"},{"time":1111000,"text":"and does cut down trees,"},{"time":1113000,"text":"the other 19 members have to decide what's going to happen to him."},{"time":1116000,"text":"If the group doesn't take action,"},{"time":1118000,"text":"the other 33 groups have to decide what is going to happen to the group"},{"time":1122000,"text":"that doesn't comply with those great deals that we are offering them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1126000,"text":"In North Sulawesi it is the cooperative --"},{"time":1129000,"text":"they have a democratic culture there,"},{"time":1131000,"text":"so there you can use the local justice system to protect your system."},{"time":1136000,"text":"In summary, if you look at it, in year one the people can sell their land"},{"time":1139000,"text":"to get income, but they get jobs back in the construction and the reforestation,"},{"time":1144000,"text":"the working with the orangutans, and they can use the waste wood to make handicraft."},{"time":1148000,"text":"They also get free land in between the trees,"},{"time":1151000,"text":"where they can grow their crops."},{"time":1153000,"text":"They can now sell part of those fruits to the orangutan project."},{"time":1157000,"text":"They get building material for houses,"},{"time":1159000,"text":"a contract for selling the sugar,"},{"time":1161000,"text":"so we can produce huge amounts of ethanol and energy locally."},{"time":1165000,"text":"They get all these other benefits: environmentally, money,"},{"time":1168000,"text":"they get education -- it's a great deal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1170000,"text":"And everything is based upon that one thing --"},{"time":1173000,"text":"make sure that forest remains there."},{"time":1176000,"text":"So if we want to help the orangutans --"},{"time":1179000,"text":"what I actually set out to do --"},{"time":1182000,"text":"we must make sure that the local people are the ones that benefit."},{"time":1186000,"text":"Now I think the real key to doing it, to give a simple answer,"},{"time":1190000,"text":"is integration."},{"time":1192000,"text":"I hope -- if you want to know more, you can read more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1196000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}